<HEAD>`Today' Wins 10th Quarterly Ratings Period In a Row</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NBC's ``Today'' show won the second quarter of
1988 in the A.C. Nielsen Co. ratings, its 10th quarterly ratings
victory in a row.
   For the second quarter of 1988, ``Today'' had an average rating
of 4.3 and a 21. ABC's ``Good Morning America'' had a 4.0 and 20,
and ``CBS This Morning'' had a 2.1 and 10.
   The rating is a percentage of the nation's 88.6 million
households with televisions. The share is a percentage of sets in
use.
   For the week ending June 24, ``Today'' had a rating of 4.1 and a
21 share. ABC's ``Good Morning America'' had a 3.5 and 18 share.
``CBS This Morning'' had a 1.9 and 10.
</TEXT>
